{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/8896", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/8896/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/8896/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/8896/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/8896", "id": 335820729, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MTk3NDIzMTcw", "number": 8896, "title": "Stop making dynamic allocations of PinnedMemoryAllocator.", "user": {"login": "ezyang", "id": 13564, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTY0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/13564?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang", "html_url": "https://github.com/ezyang", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ezyang/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2018-06-26T13:30:09Z", "updated_at": "2018-11-23T15:46:21Z", "closed_at": "2018-06-26T18:03:45Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/8896", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/8896", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/8896.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/8896.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>There is no relevant state in PinnedMemoryAllocator, so we<br>\ncan have a single allocator with static lifetime.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, this is the only use case of <code>std::unique_ptr&lt;Allocator&gt;</code>, so we revert it to <code>Allocator*</code>.</p>\n<p>Signed-off-by: Edward Z. Yang <a href=\"mailto:ezyang@fb.com\">ezyang@fb.com</a></p>\n<p>CC <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=655866\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/colesbury\">@colesbury</a></p>", "body_text": "There is no relevant state in PinnedMemoryAllocator, so we\ncan have a single allocator with static lifetime.\nFurthermore, this is the only use case of std::unique_ptr<Allocator>, so we revert it to Allocator*.\nSigned-off-by: Edward Z. Yang ezyang@fb.com\nCC @colesbury", "body": "There is no relevant state in PinnedMemoryAllocator, so we\r\ncan have a single allocator with static lifetime.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, this is the only use case of `std::unique_ptr<Allocator>`, so we revert it to `Allocator*`.\r\n\r\nSigned-off-by: Edward Z. Yang <ezyang@fb.com>\r\n\r\nCC @colesbury \r\n"}